node.text: I’ve seen all these birds so feeling fortunate. However the green Pigeon didn’t have a pink neck . Are the males and females different  or did I see another species ?

I have seen the sunbird in our garden. It loves hibiscus. I rescued a pink necked green pigeon which fell into bush next to me when the wind was v strong. I kept it for the night as it was past 9pm. It was so frightened it kept excreting purple substances, which I believe to be remnants of its berries meal. We let it go the next day as we read on Google it needed food from high ip in trees. Last week I rescued a sparrow hanging upside down from the barb wire fence of a school near my house. It was so small... surprisingly.

As we continue to #StayHomeforSG, why not try birdwatching from the comfort of your own room? Take a look outside the window, and you may spot some of our urban birds every once in a while! Check out these photos of commonly-spotted birds, like the Olive-backed Sunbird (Cinnyris jugularis), Pink-necked Green Pigeon (Treron vernans), and the Black-naped Oriole (Oriolus chinensis).⁣
⁣
From now till 5th June 2020, you can take part in our Stay-Home Birdwatching survey. Learn more about the survey and check out our Birdwatching from Home ID guide at go.gov.sg/gbwfh. Do note that all sightings have to be done from your home 😉⁣
⁣
What other feathered friends have you spotted from your window? Tell us in the comments below!⁣
⁣
